[
  [
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "From HoTT Require Import Basics Types WildCat.Core Truncations.Core Spaces.Int",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "From HoTT Require Import Basics Types WildCat.Core Truncations.Core Spaces.Int\n  AbelianGroup AbHom Centralizer AbProjective Groups.FreeGroup AbGroups.Z.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** * The free group on one generator *)\n\n(** We can define the integers as the free group on one generator, which we denote [Z1] below. Results from Centralizer.v and Groups.FreeGroup let us show that [Z1] is abelian. *)\n\n(** We define [Z1] as the free group with a single generator. *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition Z1 := FreeGroup Unit.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition Z1_gen : Z1 := freegroup_in tt.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": " (* The generator *)\n\n(** The recursion principle of [Z1] and its computation rule. *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition Z1_rec {G : Group} (g : G) : Z1 $-> G\n  := FreeGroup_rec (unit_name g).",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition Z1_rec_beta {G : Group} (g : G) : Z1_rec g Z1_gen = g\n  := FreeGroup_rec_beta _ _ _.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** The free group [Z1] on one generator is isomorphic to the subgroup of [Z1] generated by the generator.  And such cyclic subgroups are known to be commutative, by [commutative_cyclic_subgroup]. *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Instance Z1_commutative `{Funext} : Commutative (@group_sgop Z1)\n  := commutative_iso_commutative iso_subgroup_incl_freegroupon.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n(* TODO: [Funext] is used in [isfreegroupon_freegroup], but there is a comment there saying that it can be removed.  If that is done, can remove it from many results in this file. A different proof of this result, directly using the construction of the free group, could probably also avoid [Funext]. *)\n\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Definition ab_Z1 `{Funext} : AbGroup\n  := Build_AbGroup Z1 _.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": []
    },
    {
      "_type": "text",
      "contents": "\n\n(** The universal property of [ab_Z1]. *)\n"
    },
    {
      "_type": "sentence",
      "contents": "Lemma equiv_Z1_hom@{u v | u < v} `{Funext} (A : AbGroup@{u})\n  : GroupIsomorphism (ab_hom@{u v} ab_Z1@{u v} A) A.",
      "messages": [],
      "goals": [
        {
          "_type": "goal",
          "name": null,
          "conclusion": "GroupIsomorphism (ab_hom ab_Z1 A) A",
          "hypotheses": [
            {
              "_type": "hypothesis",
              "names": [
                "H"
              ],
